Content:
The Seishin-Yamate Line (, Seishin-Yamate-sen?) is one of two lines of Kobe Municipal Subway that links the central district and suburbs of Kobe. It is sometimes called U-Line after its shape on maps. All trains are based at Tanigami and Mydani Depots.
